{
  "text": "This section formulates the distributed average consensus task and briefly reviews the standard algorithms, as described in [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] . We define a graph as a 2-tuple, consisting of a set with vertices, where denotes the cardinality, and a set with edges. We denote an edge between vertices and as an unordered pair . The presence of an edge between two vertices indicates that they can establish bidirectional noise-free communication with each other. We assume that transmissions are always successful and that the topology is fixed. We assume also connected network topologies; the connectivity pattern of the graph is given by the adjacency matrix , where if otherwise.",
